Note: Expressions are like “incomplete thoughts.” Adding an equals sign turns an expression into an equation.

Order of Operations

The rules that tell us in what order to perform operations in an expression.

Rule: Parentheses → Exponents → Multiplication/Division → Addition/Subtraction (often remembered as PEMDAS).

Example: 
