📘 Polynomials and Factoring (Advanced)
3. Long Division and Synthetic Division

These are methods to divide polynomials, similar to numerical division. They are useful to:

Factor polynomials

Simplify expressions

Solve polynomial equations

3.1 Long Division of Polynomials

Polynomial long division works like numerical long division.

Steps:

Arrange both dividend and divisor in descending powers of 
𝑥
x.

Divide the leading term of the dividend by the leading term of the divisor → first term of quotient.

Multiply the divisor by this term → subtract from dividend.

Bring down the next term and repeat until the remainder has lower degree than the divisor.

