3.2 Synthetic Division

Synthetic division is a shortcut for dividing by linear divisors of the form 
𝑥
−
𝑟
x−r. It is faster than long division.

Steps:

Write down coefficients of the dividend in order. Include 0 for missing powers.

Write 
𝑟
r (from divisor 
𝑥
−
𝑟
x−r) to the left.

Bring down the first coefficient.

Multiply it by 
𝑟
r, write under the next coefficient, and add.

Repeat until all coefficients are used.

The last number is the remainder; the other numbers are coefficients of the quotient.

Example:

