6. Sketching Rational Functions

Steps:

Find vertical asymptotes (denominator = 0).

Find horizontal/slant asymptotes (end behavior).

Find x- and y-intercepts.

Check signs between asymptotes and intercepts.

Sketch the curve approaching asymptotes, passing through intercepts.

Applications of Rational Functions:

Physics: Resistance, pressure, optics (inverse square laws).

Engineering: Flow rates, gear ratios.

Economics: Supply/demand curves, cost/revenue functions.

Biology: Population models, enzyme kinetics.

