Key Takeaways

Domain restrictions correspond to impossible or undefined real-world situations (like division by zero).

Vertical asymptotes often represent thresholds, failure points, or singularities.

Holes usually indicate temporary exclusions or values that cancel out in real-world formulas.

Rational functions are powerful tools in physics, chemistry, biology, economics, and engineering.


