3. Types of Solutions

Unique Solution – lines/planes intersect at a single point.

No Solution – planes are parallel or inconsistent.

Infinitely Many Solutions – planes intersect along a line or coincide.

Check:

If determinant of coefficient matrix 
𝐴
≠
0
A

=0 → unique solution.

If determinant 
=
0
=0 → check consistency for no/infinite solutions.

4. Applications

Engineering: Forces in 3 directions, statics problems.

Economics: Solve supply-demand models with 3 products.

Physics: Motion with 3 simultaneous constraints.

Chemistry: Reaction stoichiometry with 3 unknowns.



