De Moivre’s Theorem

De Moivre’s Theorem gives a powerful way to raise complex numbers to powers or extract roots using their polar form.

1. Statement of the Theorem

If 
𝑧
=
𝑟
(
cos
⁡
𝜃
+
𝑖
sin
⁡
𝜃
)
z=r(cosθ+isinθ), then for any integer 
𝑛
