Trigonometry Basics: Angles and Radians:

1. Angles
Types of Angles
Type	Description	Example
Acute	Less than 90°	30°, 45°
Right	Exactly 90°	90°
Obtuse	Between 90° and 180°	120°
Straight	Exactly 180°	180°
Reflex	Between 180° and 360°	270°
Full rotation	360°	360°
Angle Measurement

Degrees (°) – Common in geometry.

Full circle = 360°

Right angle = 90°

Radians (rad) – Preferred in calculus/trig.

Full circle = 
