Crosses midline at the origin of the cycle.

Steep slope near asymptotes.

5. Steps to Graph

Identify amplitude, period, phase shift, vertical shift.

Draw the midline (for sine/cosine).

Mark key points for one period: max, min, midline crossings.

Sketch the wave smoothly.

For tangent: plot asymptotes first, then midline crossing.

Repeat for additional periods if needed.


