3. Waves

Sine/Cosine wave equation (traveling wave):

𝑦
(
𝑥
,
𝑡
)
=
𝐴
sin
⁡
(
𝑘
𝑥
−
𝜔
𝑡
+
𝜙
)
y(x,t)=Asin(kx−ωt+ϕ)

Where:

𝐴
A = amplitude

𝑘
=
2
𝜋
𝜆
k=
λ
2π
	​

 = wave number (
𝜆
λ = wavelength)

𝜔
=
2
𝜋
𝑓
ω=2πf = angular frequency

𝜙
ϕ = phase shift

𝑥
x = position, 
𝑡
t = time

Standing waves: Sum of two traveling waves:

𝑦
(
𝑥
,
𝑡
)
=
2
𝐴
sin
⁡
(
𝑘
𝑥
)
cos
⁡
(
𝜔
𝑡
)
y(x,t)=2Asin(kx)cos(ωt)

Nodes (no motion) occur where 
sin
⁡
(
𝑘
𝑥
)
=
0
sin(kx)=0

4. Applications in Real Life

Engineering: Vibrations of bridges, buildings, or machinery.

Physics: Pendulums, oscillating springs, circuits with AC current.

Sound & Light: Modeling waves and harmonics.

Navigation: Circular motion in orbits.